description: Actuator. An actuator is a mechanical device for moving or controlling a mechanism or system. An actuator takes energy, usually created by air, electricity, or liquid, and converts that into some kind of motion.
Electric Actuator (Actuator type). A device that electrically actuates a control element.
Hand Operated Actuator (Actuator type). A device that manually actuates a control element.
Hydraulic Actuator (Actuator type). A device that hydraulically actuates a control element.
Pneumatic Actuator (Actuator type). A device that pneumatically actuates a control element.
Thermostatic Actuator (Actuator type). A device that thermostatically actuates a control element.

Air Terminal. An air terminal is a terminating or origination point for the transfer of air between distribution system(s) and one or more spaces. It can also be used for the transfer of air between adjacent spaces.
Diffuser (Air Terminal type). An outlet discharging supply air in various directions and planes.
Grille (Air Terminal type). A covering for any area through which air passes.
Louvred Air Terminal (Air Terminal Type). A rectilinear louvre.
Register (Air Terminal type). A grille typically equipped with a damper or control valve.

Air Terminal Box. An air terminal box typically participates in an HVAC duct distribution system and is used to control or modulate the amount of air delivered to its downstream ductwork. An air terminal box type is often referred to as an "air flow regulator".
Constant Flow (Air Terminal Box type). Terminal box does not include a means to reset the volume automatically to an outside signal such as thermostat.

natural_name: Variable Flow Pressure Dependant (Air Terminal Box type)
description: Variable Flow Pressure Dependant (Air Terminal Box type). Terminal box includes a means to reset the volume automatically to a different control point in response to an outside signal such as thermostat: air-flow rate depends on supply pressure.

natural_name: Variable Flow Pressure Independant (Air Terminal Box type)
description: Variable Flow Pressure Independant (Air Terminal Box type). Terminal box includes a means to reset the volume automatically to a different control point in response to an outside signal such as thermostat: air-flow rate is independent of supply pressure.

Air to Air Heat Recovery. An air-to-air heat recovery device employs a counter-flow heat exchanger between inbound and outbound air flow. It is typically used to transfer heat from warmer air in one chamber to cooler air in the second chamber (i.e., typically used to recover heat from the conditioned air being exhausted and the outside air being supplied to a building), resulting in energy savings from reduced heating (or cooling) requirements.

natural_name: Fixed Plate Counter Flow Exchanger (Air to Air Heat Recovery type)
description: Fixed Plate Counter Flow Exchanger (Air to Air Heat Recovery type). Heat exchanger with moving parts and alternate layers of plates, separated and sealed from the exhaust and supply air stream passages with primary air entering at secondary air outlet location and exiting at secondary air inlet location.

natural_name: Fixed Plate Cross Flow Exchanger (Air to Air Heat Recovery type)
description: Fixed Plate Cross Flow Exchanger (Air to Air Heat Recovery type). Heat exchanger with moving parts and alternate layers of plates, separated and sealed from the exhaust and supply air stream passages with secondary air flow in the direction perpendicular to primary air flow.

natural_name: Fixed Plate Parallel Flow Exchanger (Air to Air Heat Recovery type)
description: Fixed Plate Parallel Flow Exchanger (Air to Air Heat Recovery type). Heat exchanger with moving parts and alternate layers of plates, separated and sealed from the exhaust and supply air stream passages with primary air entering at secondary air inlet location and exiting at secondary air outlet location.

natural_name: Heat Pipe (Air to Air Heat Recovery type)
description: Heat Pipe (Air to Air Heat Recovery type). A passive energy recovery device with a heat pipe divided into evaporator and condenser sections.

natural_name: Rotary Wheel (Air to Air Heat Recovery type)
description: Rotary Wheel (Air to Air Heat Recovery type). A heat wheel with a revolving cylinder filled with an air-permeable medium having a large internal surface area.

natural_name: Runaround Coil Loop (Air to air heat recovery type)
description: Runaround Coil Loop (Air to air heat recovery type). A typical coil energy recovery loop places extended surface, finned tube water coils in the supply and exhaust airstreams of a building.

natural_name: Thermosiphon Coil Type Heat Exchangers (Air to air heat recovery type)
description: Thermosiphon Coil Type Heat Exchangers (Air to air heat recovery type). Sealed systems that consist of an evaporator, a condenser, interconnecting piping, and an intermediate working fluid that is present in both liquid and vapor phases where the evaporator and condensor coils are installed independently in the ducts and are interconnected by the working fluid piping.

natural_name: Thermosiphon Sealed Tube Heat Exchangers (Air to Air Heat Recovery type)
description: Thermosiphon Sealed Tube Heat Exchangers (Air to Air Heat Recovery type). Sealed systems that consist of an evaporator, a condenser, interconnecting piping, and an intermediate working fluid that is present in both liquid and vapor phases where the evaporator and the condenser are usually at opposite ends of a bundle of straight, individual thermosiphon tubes and the exhaust and supply ducts are adjacent to each other.

natural_name: Twin Tower Enthalpy Recovery Loops (Air to Air Heat Recovery type)
description: Twin Tower Enthalpy Recovery Loops (Air to Air Heat Recovery type). An air-to-liquid, liquid-to-air enthalpy recovery system with a sorbent liquid circulates continuously between supply and exhaust airstreams, alternately contacting both airstreams directly in contactor towers.
Alarm. An alarm is a device that signals the existence of a condition or situation that is outside the boundaries of normal expectation or that activates such a device.
Bell (Alarm type). An audible alarm.
Break Glass Button (Alarm type). An alarm activation mechanism in which a protective glass has to be broken to enable a button to be pressed.
Light (Alarm type). A visual alarm.
Manual Pull Box (Alarm type). An alarm activation mechanism in which activation is achieved by a pulling action.
Railway Crocodile (Alarm type). An electrical contact placed between the rails (in the four-foot way) to provide warnings in the locomotive cab.

Railway Detonator (Alarm type). A coin-sized device that is used as a loud warning signal to train drivers. It is usually placed on the top of the rail, usually secured with two lead straps, one on each side.
Siren (Alarm type). An audible alarm.
Whistle (Alarm type). An audible alarm.
Audio Visual Appliance. An audio-visual appliance is a device that displays, captures, transmits, or receives audio or video.
Amplifier (Audio Visual Appliance type). A device that receives an audio signal and amplifies it to play through speakers.

Camera (Audio Visual Appliance type). A device that records images, either as a still photograph or as moving images known as videos or movies.  Note that a camera may operate with light from the visible spectrum or from other parts of the electromagnetic spectrum such as infrared or ultraviolet.

Communication Terminal (Audio Visual Appliance type). A communication terminal is an audio communication device that is usually installed along transportation infrastructure (railways, roads, tunnels etc.) in order to be used by the general public or operation agents for communication. It may specifically be used to make calls to emergency services in tunnels.
Display (Audio Visual Appliance type). An electronic device that represents information in visual form such as a flat-panel display or television.

Microphone (Audio Visual Appliance type). An acoustic-to-electric transducer or sensor that converts sound into an electrical signal.  Microphones types in use include electromagnetic induction (dynamic microphones), capacitance change (condenser microphones) or piezoelectric generation to produce the signal from mechanical vibration.
Player (Audio Visual Appliance type). A device that plays audio and/or video content directly or to another device, having fixed or removable storage media.

Projector (Audio Visual Appliance type). An apparatus for projecting a picture on a screen. Whether the device is an overhead, slide projector, or a film projector, it is usually referred to as simply a projector.
Receiver (Audio Visual Appliance type). A device that receives audio and/or video signals, switches sources, and amplifies signals to play through speakers.

Recording Equipment (Audio Visual Appliance type). A recording equipment is a device that records telephone calls or other types of audio data. It also provides the function of archiving and immediate replay.
Speaker (Audio Visual Appliance type). A loudspeaker, speaker, or speaker system is an electroacoustical transducer that converts an electrical signal to sound.
Switcher (Audio Visual Appliance type). A device that receives audio and/or video signals, switches sources, and transmits signals to downstream devices.
Telephone (Audio Visual Appliance type). A telecommunications device that is used to transmit and receive sound, and optionally video.
Tuner (Audio Visual Appliance type). An electronic receiver that detects, demodulates, and amplifies transmitted signals.

Beam. An IfcBeam is typically a horizontal, or nearly horizontal, structural member that is capable of withstanding load primarily by resisting bending. It may also represent such a member from an architectural point of view. It is not required to be load bearing.
Beam (Beam type). A standard beam usually used horizontally.
Cornice (Beam type). A non-loadbearing beam on the longitudinal edge of bridge slab, usually encasing installations.
Diaphragm (Beam type). End portion of a girder transmitting loads to supports and providing moment resistance to adjoining segment.
Edge Beam (Beam type). A beam on the longitudinal edge of bridge slab, usually concrete, providing additional stiffening and protection from the elements.
Girder Segment (Beam type). A segment of a girder (e.g. each span of a continuous girder).
Hat Stone (Beam type). A beam on top of a retaining wall or a wing wall, preventing earth movement.
Hollow Core Beam (Beam type). A wide often prestressed beam with a hollow-core profile that usually serves as a slab component.
Joist (Beam type). A beam used to support a floor or ceiling.
Lintel (Beam type). A beam or horizontal piece of material over an opening (e.g. door, window).
Pier Cap (Beam type). A transversal beam on top of a pier (on a single column or extending from one column of a pier to another column of the same pier).

Spandrel Beam (Beam type). A tall beam placed on the facade of a building. One tall side is usually finished to provide the exterior of the building. Can be used to support joists or slab elements on its interior side.

T Beam (Beam type). A beam that forms part of a slab construction and acts together with the slab which its carries. Such beams are often of T-shape (therefore the English name), but may have other shapes as well, e.g. an L-Shape or an Inverted-T-Shape.

Bearing. Type of building element that is usually used to transmit loads from superstructure to substructure, and usually allowing movement (displacement or rotation) in one or more degrees of freedom. It is typically a mechanical component procured as a whole and installed on site, but in simple cases it may be built on site (composed of other building elements, element components, etc.).
Cylindrical (Bearing type). The bearing functionality is provided by cylinder in a concave cylinder.
Disk (Bearing type). A disk bearing consist of an elastomeric disc between two metal plates.

Elastomeric (Bearing type). A pad bearing which carries vertical load by contact stresses between a sheet of sliding material and a mating surface that permits movements by sliding and accommodates rotation by deformation of the elastomer.
Guide (Bearing type). A bearing that ensures that the structure maintains the correct location or expansion/contraction path and takes no vertical load. Includes also restraint bearings.
Pot Bearing (Bearing type). A bearing which carries vertical load by compression of an (elastomeric) disc confined in a (steel) cylinder and which accommodates rotations by deformations of the disc.
Rocker (Bearing type). The bearing functionality is provided by a rocker construction. Includes line rocker and point rocker bearings.
Roller (Bearing type). The bearing functionality is provided by one or more rollers that are placed between two plates.
Spherical (Bearing type). The bearing functionality is provided by convex dome in a concave basin.

Boiler. A boiler is a closed, pressure-rated vessel in which water or other fluid is heated using an energy source such as natural gas, heating oil, or electricity. The fluid in the vessel is then circulated out of the boiler for use in various processes or heating applications.
Steam Boiler (Boiler type). Steam boiler.
Water Boiler (Boiler type). Water boiler.

Borehole. Representation of the concept of a linear geological and geotechnical model, usually an interpretation but sometimes created direct from ground penetrating measurement
The assembly may contain one of more strata and other elements such as capping and lining. The contained subtypes of IfcGeotechnicalStratum will have shape representations made from straight or bent tubes reflecting the bore diameter, or discs if a 'Yabuki' top surface model is being used.

Building Element Part. IfcBuildingElementPart represents major components as subordinate parts of a building element. Typical usage examples include precast concrete sandwich walls, where the layers may have different geometry representations. In this case the layered material representation does not sufficiently describe the element. Each layer is represented by an own instance of the IfcBuildingElementPart with its own geometry description.
Apron (Building Element Part type). A form of scour protection consisting of timber, concrete, riprap, paving, or other construction placed adjacent to abutments and piers to prevent undermining.

Armour Unit (Building Element Part type). A large quarry stone or concrete shaped unit used as erosion prevention on slopes such as revetments and breakwaters. These units are grouped together into a Course layer.
Insulation (Building Element Part type). The part provides thermal insulation, for example as insulation layer between wall panels in sandwich walls or as infill in stud walls.
Precast Panel (Building element part type). The part is a precast panel, usually as an internal or external layer in a sandwich wall panel.

Safety Cage (Building Element Part Type). Safety cages are an assembly of circular and vertical bars that are fastened to the stiles of fixed ladders and are arranged to enclose the path of a worker when climbing the ladder. Ladders so enclosed are also known as caged or hooped ladders.

Building Element Proxy. The IfcBuildingElementProxy is a proxy definition that provides the same functionality as subtypes of IfcBuildingElement, but without having a predefined meaning of the special type of building element it represents.
Complex (Building Element Proxy type). Not used - kept for upward compatibility.
Element (Building Element Proxy type). Not used - kept for upward compatibility.
Partial (Building element proxy type). Not used - kept for upward compatibility.
Burner. A burner is a device that converts fuel into heat through combustion. It includes gas, oil, and wood burners.
Cable Carrier Fitting. A cable carrier fitting is a fitting that is placed at junction or transition in a cable carrier system.
Bend (Cable Carrier Fitting type). A fitting that changes the route of the cable carrier.
Connector (Cable Carrier Fitting type). Connector fitting, typically used to join two ports together within a flow distribution system (e.g., a coupling used to join two duct segments).
Cross (Cable Carrier Fitting type). A fitting at which two branches are taken from the main route of the cable carrier simultaneously.

Junction (Cable Carrier Fitting type). A fitting with typically more than two ports used to redistribute flow among the ports and/or to change the direction of flow between connected elements (e.g, tee, cross, wye, etc.).
Tee (Cable Carrier Fitting type). A fitting at which a branch is taken from the main route of the cable carrier.
Transition (Cable Carrier Fitting type). A fitting with typically two ports having different shapes or sizes. Can also be used to change the direction of flow between connected elements.
Cable Carrier Segment. A cable carrier segment is a flow segment that is specifically used to carry and support cabling.
Cable Bracket (Cable Carrier Segment type). A cable bracket is a horizontal cable support fixed at one end only, spaced at intervals, on which cables rest.

natural_name: Cable Ladder Segment (Cable Carrier Segment type)
description: Cable Ladder Segment (Cable Carrier Segment type). An open carrier segment on which cables are carried on a ladder structure.

natural_name: Cable Tray Segment (Cable Carrier Segment type)
description: Cable Tray Segment (Cable Carrier Segment type). A (typically) open carrier segment onto which cables are laid.

natural_name: Cable Trunking Segment (Cable Carrier Segment type)
description: Cable Trunking Segment (Cable Carrier Segment type). An enclosed carrier segment with one or more compartments into which cables are placed.
Catenary Wire (Cable Carrier Segment type). A catenary wire is a longitudinal wire supporting the grooved contact wires either directly or indirectly. Note: definition from UIC 719-1.
Conduit Segment (Cable Carrier Segment type). An enclosed tubular carrier segment through which cables are pulled.
Dropper (Cable Carrier Segment type). A dropper is a cable carrier used to suspend cable from another cable. It could also conduct electricity.
Cable Fitting. A cable fitting is a fitting that is placed at a junction, transition or termination in a cable system.
Connector (Cable Fitting type). A fitting that joins two cable segments of the same connector type (though potentially different gender).
Entry (Cable Fitting type). A fitting that begins a cable segment at a non-electrical element such as a grounding clamp attached to a pipe.
Exit (Cable Fitting type). A fitting that ends a cable segment at a non-electrical element such as a grounding clamp attached to a pipe or to the ground.
Fan-out (Cable Fitting type). A fan out is a special cable fitting that provides a safe transition from multi-fiber cable units to individual fibers.
Junction (Cable Fitting type). A fitting that joins three or more segments of arbitrary connector types for signal splitting or multiplexing.
Transition (Cable Fitting type). A fitting that joins two cable segments of different connector types.
Cable Segment. A cable segment is a flow segment used to carry electrical power, data, or telecommunications signals.

Busbar Segment (Cable Segment type). Electrical conductor that makes a common connection between several electrical circuits. Properties of a busbar are the same as those of a cable segment and are captured by the cable segment property set.

Cable Segment (Cable Segment type). Cable with a specific purpose to lead electric current within a circuit or any other electric construction. Includes all types of electric cables, mainly several core segments or conductor segments wrapped together.

Conductor Segment (Cable Segment type). A single linear element within a cable or an exposed wire (such as for grounding) with the specific purpose to lead electric current, data, or a telecommunications signal.
Contact Wire Segment (Cable Segment type). An electric conductor of an overhead contact line with which the current collectors make contact. Note: definition from IEC60050 811-33-15.

Core Segment (Cable Segment type). A self contained element of a  cable that comprises one or more conductors and sheathing.The core of one lead is normally single wired or multiwired which are intertwined.
Fiber Segment (Cable Segment type). A fiber segment is an individual optical fiber used in telecommunication systems to transmit data by means of optical signals.

Fiber Tube (Cable Segment type). A fiber tube is semi-rigid hollow plastic tube with a very small radius that houses and protects a certain number of optical fiber segments. An optical cable segment may contain many fiber tubes.
Optical Cable Segment (Cable Segment type). An optical cable segment is a cable segment that contains a variable number of optical fiber segments.
Stitch Wire (Cable Segment type). A stitch wire consists of auxiliary wires and different components (clamp) used in stitched suspension.
Wire Pair Segment (Cable Segment type). A pair of conductors contained in a copper cable. The pair is always used together to form a circuit to transmit data by means of electric signals.
Caisson Foundation. CaissonFoundation essentially is a hollow box that can be either open or closed.
Caisson Foundation (Caisson Foundation type). Closed box.
Well (Caisson Foundation type). Open box.

Chiller. A chiller is a device used to remove heat from a liquid via a vapor-compression or absorption refrigeration cycle to cool a fluid, typically water or a mixture of water and glycol. The chilled fluid is then used to cool and dehumidify air in a building.
Air Cooled (Chiller type). Air cooled chiller.
Heat Recovery (Chiller type). Heat recovery chiller.
Water Cooled (Chiller type). Water cooled chiller.

Chimney. Chimneys are typically vertical, or as near as vertical, parts of the construction of a building and part of the building fabric. Often constructed by pre-cast or insitu concrete, today seldom by bricks.

Coil. A coil is a device used to provide heat transfer between non-mixing media. A common example is a cooling coil, which utilizes a finned coil in which circulates chilled water, antifreeze, or refrigerant that is used to remove heat from air moving across the surface of the coil. A coil may be used either for heating or cooling purposes by placing a series of tubes (the coil) carrying a heating or cooling fluid into an airstream. The coil may be constructed from tubes bundled in a serpentine form or from finned tubes that give a extended heat transfer surface.
DX Cooling Coil (Coil type). Cooling coil using a refrigerant to cool the air stream directly.
Electric Heating Coil (Coil type). Heating coil using electricity as a heating source.
Gas Heating Coil (Coil type). Heating coil using gas as a heating source.
Hydronic Coil (Coil type). Cooling or Heating coil that uses a hydronic fluid as a cooling or heating source.
Steam Heating Coil (Coil type). Heating coil using steam as heating source.
Water Cooling Coil (Coil type). Cooling coil using chilled water. HYDRONICCOIL supercedes this enumerator.
Water Heating Coil (Coil type). Heating coil using hot water as a heating source. HYDRONICCOIL supercedes this enumerator.

Column. An IfcColumn is a vertical structural or architectural member which often is aligned with a structural grid intersection. In most cases it represents a vertical, or nearly vertical, structural member that transmits, through compression, the weight of the structure above to other structural elements below. It may also represent such a member from an architectural point of view in which case it may represent a non load bearing element. Whether it is a structural load bearing element or a non-load bearing element is determined by the _Pset\_ColumnCommon.LoadBearing_ property.
Column (Column type). A usually vertical member that may be load bearing and requiring resistance to vertical forces by compression but also sometimes to lateral forces.

Pier Stem (Column type). An individual vertical part of a pier, may be a simple column, i.e. no breakdown into segments or separate structural parts such as flanges and web(s), or may be an aggregation of segments and/or parts.
Pier Stem Segment (Column type). A vertical segment of a pier column.
Pilaster (Column type). A column element embedded within a wall that can be required to be load bearing but may also only be used for decorative purposes.
Standard Column (Column type). A column transmitting vertical loads from superstructure to an arch below it.
Communications Appliance. A communications appliance transmits and receives electronic or digital information as data or sound.
Antenna (Communications Appliance Type). A transducer designed to transmit or receive electromagnetic waves.

Automaton (Communications Appliance type). A self-acting artificial device, the behaviour of which is governed either in a stepwise manner by given decision rules or continuously in time by defined relationships, while the output variables of which are created from its input and state variables. Note: definition from IEC 60050-351-42-32.
Computer (Communications Appliance type). A desktop, laptop, tablet, or other type of computer that can be moved from one place to another and connected to an electrical supply via a plugged outlet.
Fax (Communications Appliance type). A machine that has the primary function of transmitting a facsimile copy of printed matter using a telephone line.
Gateway (Communications Appliance type). A gateway connects multiple network segments with different protocols at all layers (layers 1-7) of the Open Systems Interconnection (OSI) model.

Intelligent Peripheral (Communications Appliance type). An intelligent peripheral is a device that offers a variety of specialized resources according to the corresponding service logical program under the control of SCP. These resources contain the receiver of DTMF (Dual-Tone Multi-Frequency, signal generator, record notice, etc.). An intelligent peripheral provides dedicated resource functions in the intelligent network, allocates, controls and manages various dedicated resources, communicates with other entities in the network, and completes SRF resource functions as well as the maintenance, management and statistics functions of resources.

IP Network Equipment (Communications Appliance Type). An IP network equipment is a device that provides IP data transmission channel for telecom subsystems or other subsystems e.g., routers, network switches or firewalls.

natural_name: Line Side Electronic Unit (Communications Appliance Type)
description: Line Side Electronic Unit (Communications Appliance Type). The lineside electronic unit (LEU) is the interface between the balise and interlocking in railway. The LEU acquires the information from the interlocking, and sends the appropriate information to the balises in concordance with the lineside signalling (if available).

Modem (Communications Appliance type). A modem (from modulator-demodulator) is a device that modulates an analog carrier signal to encode digital information, and also demodulates such a carrier signal to decode the transmitted information.
Network Appliance (Communications Appliance Type). A network appliance performs a dedicated function such as firewall protection, content filtering, load balancing, or equipment management.

Network Bridge (Communications Appliance Type). A network bridge connects multiple network segments at the data link layer (layer 2) of the OSI model, and the term layer 2 switch is very often used interchangeably with bridge.
Network Hub (Communications Appliance Type). A network hub connects multiple network segments at the physical layer (layer 1) of the OSI model.

Optical Line Terminal (Communications Appliance Type). An optical line terminal is a service provider endpoint of a passive or active optical network. It is the terminal equipment for connecting fiber optic trunks.
Optical Network Unit (Communications Appliance Type). An optical network unit is a kind of optical transmission network connection equipment which is installed at user side.
Printer (Communications Appliance type). A machine that has the primary function of printing text and/or graphics onto paper or other media.

Radio Block Center (Communications Appliance Type). A radio block center is a specialised computing device in railway with specification for generating Movement Authorities (MA) and transmitting it to trains. It gets information from signalling control and from the trains in its section.

Repeater (Communications Appliance type). A repeater is an electronic device that receives a signal and retransmits it at a higher level and/or higher power, or onto the other side of an obstruction, so that the signal can cover longer distances without degradation.

Router (Communications Appliance Type). A router is a networking device whose software and hardware are usually tailored to the tasks of routing and forwarding information. For example, on the Internet, information is directed to various paths by routers.
Scanner (Communications Appliance type). A machine that has the primary function of scanning the content of printed matter and converting it to digital format that can be stored in a computer.

Telecommand (Communications Appliance Type). A system sending command to control and monitor the switches and circuit breakers or systems directly or not connected (e.g. via wires) within the traction power system remotely.
Telephony Exchange (Communications Appliance Type). A telephony exchange is a device that ensures the routing of telephone calls and communications.

Transition Component (Communications Appliance Type). A transition component is a minor active device that converts electric signals to optical signals at the sender, and converts optical signals to electric signals at the receiver.

Transponder (Communications Appliance Type). A transponder is a communication, monitoring, or control device that, upon receiving a signal, emits a different signal in response. Transponders can be either passive or active (e.g., electronic beacon, balise).

Transport Equipment (Communications Appliance Type). A transport equipment is a network element responsible for providing functionality of transport, multiplexing, switching, management and supervision of transmission channels between different hosts. The data transport service uses three specific metrics: the bandwidth, the jitter, and the packet loss rate.
Compressor. A compressor is a device that compresses a fluid typically used in a refrigeration circuit.
Booster (Compressor type). Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where pressure is increased by a booster.

Dynamic (Compressor type). The pressure of refrigerant vapor is increased by a continuous transfer of angular momentum from a rotating member to the vapor followed by conversion of this momentum into static pressure.

Hermetic (Compressor type). Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where the motor and compressor are contained within the same housing, with the motor shaft integral with the compressor crankshaft and the motor in contact with refrigerant.
Open Type (Compressor type). Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where the shaft extends through a seal in the crankcase for an external drive.
Reciprocating (Compressor type). Positive-displacement compressor using a piston driven by a connecting rod from a crankshaft.
Rolling Piston (Compressor type). Positive-displacement rotary compressor using a roller mounted on the eccentric of a shaft with a single vane in the nonrotating cylindrical housing.
Rotary (Compressor type). Positive-displacement compressor using a roller or rotor device.
Rotary Vane (Compressor type). Positive-displacement rotary compressor using a roller mounted on the eccentric of a shaft with multiple vanes in the nontotating cylindrical housing.
Scroll Compressor (Compressor type). Positive-displacement compressor using two inter-fitting, spiral-shaped scroll members.
Semi Hermetic (Compressor type). Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where the hermetic compressors use bolted construction amenable to field repair.
Single Screw (Compressor type). Positive-displacement rotary compressor using a single cylindrical main rotor that works with a pair of gate rotors.
Single Stage (Compressor type). Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where vapor is compressed in a single stage.

Trochoidal Compressor (Compressor type). Positive-displacement compressor using a rolling motion of one circle outside or inside the circumference of a basic circle and produce either epitrochoids or hypotrochoids.

Twin Screw (Compressor type). Positive-displacement rotary compressor using two mating helically grooved rotors, male (lobes) and female (flutes) in a stationary housing with inlet and outlet gas ports.
Welded Shell Hermetic (Compressor type). Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where the motor compressor is mounted inside a steel shell, which, in turn is sealed by welding.
Condenser. A condenser is a device that is used to dissipate heat, typically by condensing a substance such as a refrigerant from its gaseous to its liquid state.
Air Cooled (Condenser type). A condenser in which heat is transferred to an air-stream.
Evaporative Cooled (Condenser type). A condenser that is cooled evaporatively.
Water Cooled (Condenser type). Water-cooled condenser with unspecified operation.
Water Cooled Brazed Plate (Condenser type). Water-cooled condenser with plates brazed together to form an assembly of separate channels.
Water Cooled Shell Coil (Condenser type). Water-cooled condenser with cooling water circulated through one or more continuous or assembled coils contained within the shell.
Water Cooled Shell Tube (Condenser type). Water-cooled condenser with cooling water circulated through one or more tubes contained within the shell.

natural_name: Water Cooled Tube In Tube (Condenser type)
description: Water Cooled Tube In Tube (Condenser type). Water-cooled condenser consisting of one or more assemblies of two tubes, one within the other.
Controller. A controller is a device that monitors inputs and controls outputs within a building automation system.
Floating (Controller type). Output increases or decreases at a constant or accelerating rate.
Multi Position (Controller type). Output is discrete value, can be one of three or more values.
Programmable (Controller type). Output is programmable such as Discrete Digital Control (DDC).
Proportional Controller (Controller type). Output is proportional to the control error and optionally time integral and derivative.
Two Position (Controller type). Output can be either on or off.

Conveyor Segment. A conveyor segment defines an occurrence of a flow segment/ continuous run within a conveyor system that joins two sections of the system. these can utilise different carrying methods such as belt, rope, chain, screw etc. Also refers to a machine that continuously transports material or objects along a gentle slope using an endless belt, rope or chain, or rollers.
Belt Conveyor (Conveyor Segment type). An endless belt for carrying material without stretching.
Bucket Conveyor (Conveyor Segment type). A conveyor in the form of connected buckets or segments that move in a continuous loop
Chute Conveyor (Conveyor Segment type). Gravity-operated conveyor where media descends through a trough or chute.
Screw Conveyor (Conveyor Segment type). composed of a longitudinal screw in a trough or pipe that rotates to force media through the segment

Cooled Beam. A cooled beam (or chilled beam) is a device typically used to cool air by circulating a fluid such as chilled water through exposed finned tubes above a space. Typically mounted overhead near or within a ceiling, the cooled beam uses convection to cool the space below it by acting as a heat sink for the naturally rising warm air of the space. Once cooled, the air naturally drops back to the floor where the cycle begins again.
Active Cooled Beam (Cooled Beam type). An active or ventilated cooled beam provides cooling (and heating) but can also function as an air terminal in a ventilation system.
Passive Cooled Beam (Cooled Beam type). A passive or static cooled beam provides cooling (and heating) to a room or zone.
Cooling Tower. A cooling tower is a device which rejects heat to ambient air by circulating a fluid such as water through it to reduce its temperature by partial evaporation.
Mechanical Forced Draft (Cooling Tower type). Air flow is produced by a mechanical device, typically one or more fans, located on the inlet air side of the cooling tower.
Mechanical Induced Draft (Cooling Tower type). Air flow is produced by a mechanical device, typically one or more fans, located on the air outlet side of the cooling tower.
Natural Draft (Cooling Tower type). Air flow is produced naturally.

Course. A built element whose length greatly exceeds its thickness and often also its width, usually of a single material laid on site on top of another horizontal or nearly horizontal built element. A course is distinctive from a earthworks element in that a course is a graded granular (which can be bound or unbound) material that is generally processed in some fashion, where as earthworks elements are soil earthen based structure that can be formed by removal and transport of general ground material.
Structurally a course does not have capacity to carry loads over open span, or to be removed or replaced as a single unit. examples of courses include:
* Graded aggregate layers
* Graded sand layers
* Cement bounded material (CBM)
* Asphalt layers
Armour (Course type). An Aggregate layer whose primary function is to protect against erosion of the underlying material by water e.g. riprap.
Ballast Bed (Course type). Layer composed of broken stones under the sleepers.
Core (Course type). A core course is the bulk internal structure of aggregate structures.
Filter (Course type). An Intermediate layer whose primary function is to prevent the washing through of fine materials.
Pavement (Course type). A layer within a pavement structure that forms a paved area or road.
Protection (Course type). Layer with the primary task to provide protection against erosion and scour.

Covering. A covering is an element which covers some part of another element and is fully dependent on that other element. The IfcCovering defines the occurrence of a covering type, that (if given) is expressed by the IfcCoveringType.
Ceiling (Covering type). The covering is used to represent a ceiling.
Cladding (Covering type). The covering is used to represent a cladding.
Coping (Covering type). A protective capping or covering of a wall or a parapet.
Flooring (Covering type). The covering is used to represent a flooring.
Insulation (Covering type). The covering is used to insulate an element for thermal or acoustic purposes.

Membrane (Covering type). An impervious layer that could be used for e.g. roof covering (below tiling - that may be known as sarking etc.) or as a damp proof course membrane; also, waterproofing material on a bridge structure (typically on top of bridge slab).
Molding (Covering type). The covering is used to represent a molding being a strip of material to cover the transition of surfaces (often between wall cladding and ceiling).
Roofing (Covering type). The covering is used to represent a roof covering.
Skirting Board (Covering type). The covering is used to represent a skirting board being a strip of material to cover the transition between the wall cladding and the flooring.
Sleeving (Covering type). The covering is used to isolate a distribution element from a space in which it is contained.
Topping (Covering type). A layer of material used for leveling or flattening a surface.
Wrapping (Covering type). The covering is used for wrapping particularly of distribution elements using tape.

Curtain Wall. A curtain wall is a wall of a building which is an assembly of components, hung from the edge of the floor/roof structure rather than bearing on a floor. Curtain wall is represented as a building element assembly and implemented as a subtype of IfcBuildingElement that uses an IfcRelAggregates relationship. A curtain wall is often external, but using Pset_CurtainWallCommon.IsExternal can be used to define interior curtain walls.
Damper. A damper typically participates in an HVAC duct distribution system and is used to control or modulate the flow of air.
Backdraft Damper (Damper type). Damper used for purposes of manually balancing pressure differences.  Commonly operated by mechanical adjustment.
Balancing Damper (Damper type). Backdraft damper used to restrict the movement of air in one direction.  Commonly operated by mechanical spring.
Blast Damper (Damper type). Blast damper used to prevent protect occupants and equipment against overpressures resultant of an explosion.  Commonly operated by mechanical spring.
Control Damper (Damper type). Control damper used to modulate the flow of air by adjusting the position of the blades.  Commonly operated by an actuator of a building automation system.
Fire Damper (Damper type). Fire damper used to prevent the spread of fire for a specified duration.  Commonly operated by fusable link that melts above a certain temperature.
Fire Smoke Damper (Damper type). Combination fire and smoke damper used to prevent the spread of fire and smoke.  Commonly operated by a fusable link and a smoke detector.
Fume Hood Exhaust (Damper type). Fume hood exhaust damper.  Commonly operated by actuator.
Gravity Damper (Damper type). Gravity damper closes from the force of gravity.  Commonly operated by gravitational weight.

Gravity Relief Damper (Damper type). Gravity-relief damper used to allow air to move upon a buildup of enough pressure to overcome the gravitational force exerted upon the damper blades.  Commonly operated by gravitational weight.
Relief Damper (Damper type). Relief damper used to allow air to move upon a buildup of a specified pressure differential.  Commonly operated by mechanical spring.
Smoke Damper (Damper type). Smoke damper used to prevent the spread of smoke.  Commonly operated by a smoke detector of a building automation system.

Deep Foundation. Deep foundation is a type of foundation that transfers loads deeper than shallow foundation below the soft soils not capable of bearing the above structure. Depending on the soil strength it might have to reach down to the rock layer.
Discrete Accessory. A discrete accessory is a representation of different kinds of accessories included in or added to elements.

Anchor Plate (Discrete Accessory type). An accessory consisting of a steel plate, shear stud connectors or welded-on rebar which is embedded into the surface of a concrete element so that other elements can be welded or bolted onto it later.

Bird Protection (Discrete Accessory type). A device that prevents a sitting down of birds at electrically critical points and thus birds are protected against electrical shocks and disturbances by short circuit are avoided.
Bracket (Discrete Accessory type). An L-shaped or similarly shaped accessory attached in a corner between elements to hold them together or to carry a secondary element.

Cable Arranger (Discrete Accessory type). A cable arranger is a flexible accessory or a part of a component placed around cables to arrange and minimize flexing of them at the point where it is placed.

Elastic Cushion (Discrete Accessory type). A track elastic cushion is a kind of layer set on grooved sides of a concrete base, which is used for mitigating the impact of longitudinal and lateral load on track structures. A track elastic cushion shall only appear in ballastless track structures.
Expansion Joint Device (Discrete Accessory Type). Assembly connection element between construction elements to allow for thermic differential expansions.
Filler (Discrete Accessory type). Sealant, gap filler rod, packing material or other used to close a gap.
Flashing (Discrete Accessory type). Construction material used to manage the passage of water around objects.
Insulator (Discrete Accessory type). A device designed to support and insulate a conductive element. Note: definition from IEC 151-15-39.

Lock (Discrete Accessory type). A lock is a mechanical or electronic fastening device that is released either by a physical object (e.g., key, fingerprint, RFID card, security token etc.), by supplying secret information (e.g., number permutation, password), or by a combination thereof.
Panel Strengthening (Discrete Accessory type). A component that minimizes pump effects of the substructure.

natural_name: Point Machine Mounting Device (Discrete Accessory Type)
description: Point Machine Mounting Device (Discrete Accessory Type). Point machine mounting device.

natural_name: Point Machine Locking Device (Discrete Accessory Type)
description: Point Machine Locking Device (Discrete Accessory Type). Point machine locking device.
Rail Brace (Discrete Accessory type). A rail component that prevents rails from tipping and twisting.
Rail Pad (Discrete Accessory type). A non-metallic pad placed between rail and baseplate or rail and sleeper, bearer or slab. Note: definition from EN 13481-1.

Rail Lubrication (Discrete Accessory type). A device that prevents wearing of the rails throughout the flange of wheel to reduce noise emissions. It is often located at inner side of the outer rail in a curve or near turnouts (depends on function wearing or noise reduction).

Rail Mechanical Equipment (Discrete Accessory Type). A rail mechanical equipment is a mechnical equipment installed at railside, like blocking device, speed regulator, bias loaded inspector, track scale or controllable retarder.
Shoe (Discrete Accessory type). A column shoe or a beam shoe (beam hanger) used to support or secure an element.
Sliding Chair (Discrete Accessory Type). A component which supports and retains the stock rail and a flat surface upon which the foot of the switch rail slides.
Sound Absorption (Discrete Accessory type). A component in the track for sound absorption and may also absorb vibrations. It is often used in combination with slab tracks.
Tensioning Equipment (Discrete Accessory type). An equipment used to maintain the tension of conductors or cables.
Distribution Board. A distribution board is a flow controller in which instances of electrical or communication devices are brought together at a single place for a particular purpose.
Consumer Unit (Distribution Board type). A distribution point on the incoming electrical supply, typically in domestic premises, at which protective devices are located.
Dispatching Board (Distribution Board type). A distribution point at which voice and data communication signals are managed between communication devices.
Distribution Board (Distribution Board Type). A distribution point at which connections are made for distribution of electrical circuits usually through protective devices.

Distribution Frame (Distribution Board type). A distribution frame is used to interconnect and manage wiring between active equipment and subscriber. It might be composed of multiple distribution boards and other components.
Motor Control Centre (Distribution Board Type). A distribution point at which starting and control devices for major plant items are located.
Switchboard (Distribution Board Type). A distribution point at which switching devices are located.
Distribution Chamber Element. A distribution chamber element defines a place at which distribution systems and their constituent elements may be inspected or through which they may travel.
Formed Duct (Distribution Chamber Element type). Space formed in the ground for the passage of pipes, cables, ducts.
Inspection Chamber (Distribution Chamber Element type). Chamber constructed on a drain, sewer or pipeline with a removable cover that permits visible inspection.
Inspection Pit (Distribution Chamber Element type). Recess or chamber formed to permit access for inspection of substructure and services.
Manhole (Distribution Chamber Element type). Chamber constructed on a drain, sewer or pipeline with a removable cover that permits the entry of a person.
Meter Chamber (Distribution Chamber Element type). Chamber that houses a meter(s).
Sump (Distribution Chamber Element type). Recessed or small chamber into which liquid is drained to facilitate its collection for removal.
Trench (Distribution Chamber Element type). Excavated chamber, the length of which typically exceeds the width.
Valve Chamber (Distribution Chamber Element type). Chamber that houses a valve(s).

Distribution Control Element. The distribution element IfcDistributionControlElement defines occurrence elements of a building automation control system that are used to impart control over elements of a distribution system.

Distribution Flow Element. The distribution element IfcDistributionFlowElement defines occurrence elements of a distribution system that facilitate the distribution of energy or matter, such as air, water or power.

Door. The door is a built element that is predominately used to provide controlled access for people, goods, animals and vehicles. It includes constructions with hinged, pivoted, sliding, and additionally revolving and folding operations. A door can:
Boom Barrier (Door type). A boom barrier (also known as a boom gate) is a bar, or pole pivoted to allow the boom to block vehicular or pedestrian access through a controlled point.
Door (Door type). A standard door usually within a wall opening, as a door panel in a curtain wall, or as a "free standing" door.
Gate (Door type). A gate is a point of entry into a space usually within an opening in a fence. Or as a "free standing" gate.
Trap Door (Door type). A special door that lies horizonally in a slab opening. Often used for accessing cellar or attic.
Turnstile (Door type). A mechanical gate consisting of revolving arms, allowing only one person at a time to pass through.

Duct Fitting. A duct fitting is a junction or transition in a ducted flow distribution system or used to connect duct segments, resulting in changes in flow characteristics to the fluid such as direction and flow rate.
Bend (Duct fitting type). A fitting with typically two ports used to change the direction of flow between connected elements.
Connector (Duct fitting type). Connector fitting, typically used to join two ports together within a flow distribution system (e.g., a coupling used to join two duct segments).
Entry (Duct fitting type). Entry fitting, typically unconnected at one port and connected to a flow distribution system at the other (e.g., an outside air duct system intake opening).
Exit (Duct Fitting type). Exit fitting, typically unconnected at one port and connected to a flow distribution system at the other (e.g., an exhaust air discharge opening).

Junction (Duct fitting type). A fitting with typically more than two ports used to redistribute flow among the ports and/or to change the direction of flow between connected elements (e.g, tee, cross, wye, etc.).
Obstruction (Duct Fitting type). A fitting with typically two ports used to obstruct or restrict flow between the connected elements (e.g., screen, perforated plate, etc.).
Transition (Duct fitting type). A fitting with typically two ports having different shapes or sizes. Can also be used to change the direction of flow between connected elements.
Duct Segment. A duct segment is used to typically join two sections of duct network.
Flexible Segment (Duct Segment type). A flexible segment is a continuous non-linear segment of duct that can be deformed and change the direction of flow.
Rigid Segment (Duct Segment type). A rigid segment is a continuous linear segment of duct that cannot be deformed.

Duct Silencer. A duct silencer is a device that is typically installed inside a duct distribution system for the purpose of reducing the noise levels from air movement, fan noise, etc. in the adjacent space or downstream of the duct silencer device.
Flat Oval (Duct Silencer type). Flat-oval shaped duct silencer type.
Rectangular (Duct Silencer type). Rectangular shaped duct silencer type.
Round (Duct Silencer type). Round duct silencer type.

Earthworks Cut. The resulting void from modification of existing terrain or road structure by excavation or by other means of removing material. Also refers to a void that results from bulk excavation of material. The material excavated and either used as fill or discarded as waste is not modelled as Cut, but may be handled as a different concept (Resource) in the future.
Base Excavation (Earthworks Cut type). Excavation for basements of buildings, abutments of bridges or similar structures either partially or completely below ground level.

Cut (Earthworks Cut type). Excavation where soil or rock below topsoil is cut to the depth required for the construction of facilities such as roads and railways. The removed material can be used as fill (IfcEarthworksElement) for embankments or to form a level surface on which to build.
Dredging (Earthworks Cut type). Underwater excavation to recover material or to create a greater depth of water.
Excavation (Earthworks cut type). General type of excavation when more accurate type is not specified.
Over Excavation (Earthworks Cut type). Excavation that goes beyond the depth required for construction, in order to replace unsuitable material.
Pavement Milling (Earthworks Cut type). Removal of expired material from top of pavement to be replaced by new material.
Step Excavation (Earthworks cut type). Removal of the soft part of the existing road slope, where it is dug into steps, when widening a road.

Topsoil Removal (Earthworks cut type). Excavation where the topmost layer of soil containing organic material is cut or stripped. The removed topsoil can be used as fill (EarthworksElement) e.g. where planting is planned.
Trench (Earthworks cut type). Excavation whose length greatly exceeds the depth and width. Trench is typically excavated for strip foundations or for buried services such as drainage or cabling.

Earthworks Element. A type of built element created by earthwork activities to build subgrade, to raise the level of the ground in general or reinforce or stabilize soil by some mechanical or chemical method.
Earthworks Fill. A type of earthworks element created by earthwork activities to build subgrade or to raise the level of the ground in general.
Backfill (Earthworks Fill type). Fill behind retaining walls or other structures such as quays, behind abutments and bridges.
Counterweight (Earthworks Fill type). Embankment built on the side of the main road structure to reduce the settlement of the road.

Embankment (Earthworks Fill type). Predominantly longitudinal type of earthworks element with no other particular assigned type according to its role in Pavement or Subgrade. Also refers to a section of earthworks, often formed by cut or fill, where the finished ground level is above or below original ground level and whose length usually greatly exceeds its width.
Slope Fill (Earthworks Fill type). Side slope (batter) fill abutting the road structure or back slope fill.

Subgrade (Earthworks Fill type). Type of earthworks element forming the structure below pavement and above natural soil. Also refers to upper part of the soil, natural or constructed, that supports the loads transmitted by the overlying structure of a road, runway, or similar hard surface. Also refers to upper layer of the natural ground upon which the pavement is constructed.
Subgrade Bed (Earthworks Fill type). Upper part of the soil, natural or constructed, that supports the loads transmitted by the overlying structure of a road, runway, or similar hard surface.

Transition Section (Earthworks Fill type). Section of subgrade to ensure the consistency of stiffness and prevent uneven settlement. Transition section may appear e.g. between: embankment and bridge abutment
Electric Appliance. An electric appliance is a device intended for consumer usage that is powered by electricity.
Dishwasher (Electric Appliance Type). An appliance that has the primary function of washing dishes.
Electric Cooker (Electric Appliance Type). An electrical appliance that has the primary function of cooking food (including oven, hob, grill).

Freestanding Electric Heater (Electric Appliance Type). An electrical appliance that is used occasionally to provide heat. A freestanding electric heater is a 'plugged' appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.

Freestanding Fan (Electric Appliance Type). An electrical appliance that is used occasionally to provide ventilation. A freestanding fan is a 'plugged' appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.

Freestanding Water Cooler (Electric Appliance type). A small, local electrical appliance for cooling water. A freestanding water cooler is a 'plugged' appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.

Freestanding Water Heater (Electric Appliance type). A small, local electrical appliance for heating water. A freestanding water heater is a 'plugged' appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.
Freezer (Electric Appliance Type). An electrical appliance that has the primary function of storing food at temperatures below the freezing point of water.
Fridge Freezer (Electric Appliance Type). An electrical appliance that combines the functions of a freezer and a refrigerator through the provision of separate compartments.
Hand Dryer (Electric Appliance Type). An electrical appliance that has the primary function of drying hands.
Kitchen Machine (Electric Appliance Type). A specialized appliance used in commercial kitchens such as a mixer.
Microwave (Electric Appliance Type). An electrical appliance that has the primary function of cooking food using microwaves.
Photocopier (Electric Appliance Type). A machine that has the primary function of reproduction of printed matter.
Refrigerator (Electric Appliance Type). An electrical appliance that has the primary function of storing food at low temperature but above the freezing point of water.
Tumble Dryer (Electric Appliance Type). An electrical appliance that has the primary function of drying clothes.
Vending Machine (Electric Appliance Type). An appliance that stores and vends goods including food, drink, tickets, and goods of various types.
Washing Machine (Electric Appliance Type). An appliance that has the primary function of washing clothes.
Electric Distribution Board. A distribution board is a flow controller in which instances of electrical devices are brought together at a single place for a particular purpose.
Consumer Unit (Electric Distribution Board type). A distribution point on the incoming electrical supply, typically in domestic premises, at which protective devices are located.
Distribution Board (Electric Distribution Board type). A distribution point at which connections are made for distribution of electrical circuits usually through protective devices.

natural_name: Motor Control Centre (Electric Distribution Board type)
description: Motor Control Centre (Electric Distribution Board type). A distribution point at which starting and control devices for major plant items are located.
Switchboard (Electric Distribution Board type). A distribution point at which switching devices are located.
Electric Flow Storage Device. An electric flow storage device is a device in which electrical energy is stored and from which energy may be progressively released.
Battery (Electric Flow Storage Device type). A device for storing energy in chemical form so that it can be released as electrical energy.

Capacitor (Electric Flow Storage Device type). A device that stores electric charge when an external power supply is present using the electrical property of capacitance. Two-terminal device characterized essentially by its capacitance. Note: definition from IEC 60050 151-13-28.

natural_name: Capacitor Bank (Electric Flow Storage Device type)
description: Capacitor Bank (Electric Flow Storage Device type). A device that stores electrical energy when an external power supply is present using the electrical property of capacitance.
Compensator (Electric Flow Storage Device type). A device that is used to fix or adjust the parameter of electric energy, such as voltage loss, power factor and so on.

natural_name: Harmonic Filter (Electric Flow Storage Device type)
description: Harmonic Filter (Electric Flow Storage Device type). A device that constantly injects currents that precisely correspond to the harmonic components drawn by the load.
Inductor (Electric Flow Storage Device type). A device used in circuits or power systems due to their inductance, acting as a component of electric storage device.

natural_name: Inductor Bank (Electric Flow Storage Device type)
description: Inductor Bank (Electric Flow Storage Device type). A device that stores electrical energy in a magnetic field using electrical property of inductance.
Recharger (Electric Flow Storage Device type). A recharger or battery charger is a device used to put energy into a secondary cell or rechargeable battery by forcing an electric current through it.

natural_name: Uninterruptible Power Supply (Electric Flow Storage Device type)
description: Uninterruptible Power Supply (Electric Flow Storage Device type). A device that provides a time limited alternative source of power supply in the event of failure of the main supply.
Electric Flow Treatment Device. An electric flow treatment device is used to remove unwanted matter from an electric or electronic signal in a flow distribution system.

natural_name: Electronic Filter (Electric Flow Treatment Device type)
description: Electronic Filter (Electric Flow Treatment Device type). Linear two-port device designed to transmit spectral components of the input quantity according to a specified law, generally in order to pass the components in certain frequency bands and to attenuate those in other bands
Electric Generator. An electric generator is an engine that is a machine for converting mechanical energy into electrical energy.

natural_name: Combined Heat and Power (Electric Generator type)
description: Combined Heat and Power (Electric Generator type). Combined heat and power supply, used not only as a source of electric energy but also as a heating source for the building. It may therefore be not only part of an electrical system but also of a heating system.
Engine Generator (Electric Generator Type). Electrical generator with a fuel-driven engine, for example a diesel-driven emergency power supply.
Standalone (Electric Generator type). Electrical generator which does not include its source of kinetic energy, that is, a motor, engine, or turbine are all modeled separately.
Electric Motor. An electric motor is an engine that is a machine for converting electrical energy into mechanical energy.
DC (Electric Motor type). A motor using either generated or rectified Direct Current (DC) power.

Induction (Electric Motor type). An alternating current motor in which the primary winding on one member (usually the stator) is connected to the power source and a secondary winding or a squirrel-cage secondary winding on the other member (usually the rotor) carries the induced current. There is no physical electrical connection to the secondary winding, its current is induced.
Polyphase (Electric motor type). A two or three-phase induction motor in which the windings, one for each phase, are evenly divided by the same number of electrical degrees.

Reluctance Synchronous (Electric Motor type). A synchronous motor with a special rotor design which directly lines the rotor up with the rotating magnetic field of the stator, allowing for no slip under load.
Synchronous (Electric Motor type). A motor that operates at a constant speed up to full load. The rotor speed is equal to the speed of the rotating magnetic field of the stator
Electric Time Control. An electric time control is a device that applies control to the provision or flow of electrical energy over time.
Relay (Electric Time Control type). Electromagnetically operated contactor for making or breaking a control circuit.
Time Clock (Electric Time Control type). A control that causes action to occur at set times.
Time Delay (Electric Time Control type). A control that causes action to occur following a set duration.

Energy Conversion Device. The distribution flow element IfcEnergyConversionDevice defines the occurrence of a device used to perform energy conversion or heat transfer and typically participates in a flow distribution system. Its type is defined by IfcEnergyConversionDeviceType or its subtypes.
Engine. An engine is a device that converts fuel into mechanical energy through combustion.
External Combustion (Engine type). Combustion is external.
Internal Combustion (Engine type). Combustion is internal.
Evaporative Cooler. An evaporative cooler is a device that cools air by saturating it with water vapor.

natural_name: Direct Evaporative Air Washer (Evaporative Cooler Type)
description: Direct Evaporative Air Washer (Evaporative Cooler Type). Direct evaporative air washer: Cools the air stream by evaporating water dircectly into the air stream using coolers with spray-type air washer consist of a chamber or casing containing spray nozzles, and tank for collecting spray water, and an eliminator section for removing entrained drops of water from the air.

natural_name: Direct Evaporative Packaged Rotary Air Cooler (Evaporative Cooler Type)
description: Direct Evaporative Packaged Rotary Air Cooler (Evaporative Cooler Type). Direct evaporative packaged rotary air cooler: Cools the air stream by evaporating water dircectly into the air stream using coolers that wet and wash the evaporative pad by rotating it through a water bath.

natural_name: Direct Evaporative Random Media Air Cooler (Evaporative Cooler Type)
description: Direct Evaporative Random Media Air Cooler (Evaporative Cooler Type). Direct evaporative random media air cooler: Cools the air stream by evaporating water dircectly into the air stream using coolers with evaporative pads, usually of aspen wood or plastic fiber/foam.

natural_name: Direct Evaporative Rigid Media Air Cooler (Evaporative Cooler type)
description: Direct Evaporative Rigid Media Air Cooler (Evaporative Cooler type). Direct evaporative rigid media air cooler: Cools the air stream by evaporating water dircectly into the air stream using coolers with sheets of rigid, corrugated material as the wetted surface.

natural_name: Direct Evaporative Slingers Packaged Air Cooler (Evaporative Cooler Type)
description: Direct Evaporative Slingers Packaged Air Cooler (Evaporative Cooler Type). Direct evaporative slingers packaged air cooler: Cools the air stream by evaporating water dircectly into the air stream using coolers with a water slinger in an evaporative cooling section and a fan section.

Indirect Direct Combination (Evaporative Cooler type). Indirect/Direct combination: Cools the air stream by evaporating water indirectly and without adding moisture into the air stream using a two-stage cooler with a first-stage indirect evaporative cooler and second-stage direct evaporative cooler.

natural_name: Indirect Evaporative Cooling Tower or Coil Cooler (Evaporative Cooler Type)
description: Indirect Evaporative Cooling Tower or Coil Cooler (Evaporative Cooler Type). Indirect evaporative cooling tower or coil cooler: Cools the air stream by evaporating water indirectly and without adding moisture into the air stream using a combination of a cooling tower or other evaporative water cooler with a water-to-air heat exchanger coil and water circulating pump.

natural_name: Indirect Evaporative Package Air Cooler (Evaporative Cooler type)
description: Indirect Evaporative Package Air Cooler (Evaporative Cooler type). Indirect evaporative package air cooler: Cools the air stream by evaporating water indirectly and without adding moisture into the air stream. On one side of the heat exchanger, the secondary air stream is cooled by evaporation, while on the other side of heat exchanger, the primary air stream (conditioned air to be supplied to the room) is sensibly cooled by the heat exchanger surfaces.

natural_name: Indirect Evaporative Wet Coil (Evaporative Cooler Type)
description: Indirect Evaporative Wet Coil (Evaporative Cooler Type). Indirect evaporative wet coil: Cools the air stream by evaporating water indirectly and without adding moisture into the air stream. Water is sprayed directly on the tubes of the heat exchanger where latent cooling takes place and the vaporization of the water on the outside of the heat exchanger tubes allows the simultaneous heat and mass transfer which removes heat from the supply air on the tube side.
Evaporator. An evaporator is a device in which a liquid refrigerent is vaporized and absorbs heat from the surrounding fluid.
Direct Expansion (Evaporator type). Direct-expansion evaporator.
Direct Expansion Brazed Plate (Evaporator type). Direct-expansion evaporator where a refrigerant evaporates inside plates brazed or welded together to make up an assembly of separate channels.

natural_name: Direct Expansion Shell and Tube (Evaporator type)
description: Direct Expansion Shell and Tube (Evaporator type). Direct-expansion evaporator where a refrigerant evaporates inside a series of baffles that channel the fluid throughout the shell side.

natural_name: Direct Expansion Tube In Tube (Evaporator type)
description: Direct Expansion Tube In Tube (Evaporator type). Direct-expansion evaporator where a refrigerant evaporates inside one or more pairs of coaxial tubes.
Flooded Shell and Tube (Evaporator type). Evaporator in which refrigerant evaporates outside tubes.
Shell and Coil (Evaporator type). Evaporator in which refrigerant evaporates inside a simple coiled tube immersed in the fluid to be cooled.
Fan. A fan is a device which imparts mechanical work on a gas. A typical usage of a fan is to induce airflow in a building services air distribution system.
Centrifugal Airfoil (Fan type). Air flows through the impeller radially using blades that are airfoil shaped.
Centrifugal Backward Inclined Curved (Fan type). Air flows through the impeller radially using blades that are backward curved.
Centrifugal Forward Curved (Fan type). Air flows through the impeller radially using blades that are forward curved.
Centrifugal Radial (Fan type). Air flows through the impeller radially using blades that are uncurved or slightly forward curved.
Propellor Axial (Fan type). Air flows through the impeller axially and small hub-to-tip ratio impeller mounted in an orifice plate or inlet ring.
Tube Axial (Fan type). Air flows through the impeller axially with reduced tip clearance and operating at higher tip speeds.
Vane Axial (Fan type). Air flows through the impeller axially with guide vanes and reduced running blade tip clearance.

Fastener. Representations of fixing parts which are used as fasteners to connect or join elements with other elements. Excluded are mechanical fasteners which are modeled by a separate entity (IfcMechanicalFastener).
Glue (Fastener type). A fastening connection where glue is used to join together elements.
Mortar (Fastener type). A composition of mineralic or other materials used to fill jointing gaps and possibly fulfilling a load carrying role.
Weld (Fastener type). A weld seam between parts of metallic material or other suitable materials.

Feature Element Addition. A feature element addition is a specialization of the general feature element, that represents an existence dependent element which modifies the shape and appearance of the associated master element. The IfcFeatureElementAddition offers the ability to handle shape modifiers as semantic objects within the IFC object model that add to the shape of the master element.

Feature Element Subtraction. The IfcFeatureElementSubtraction is specialization of the general feature element, that represents an existence dependent elements which modifies the shape and appearance of the associated master element. The IfcFeatureElementSubtraction offers the ability to handle shape modifiers as semantic objects within the IFC object model that subtract from the shape of the master element.
Filter. A filter is an apparatus used to remove particulate or gaseous matter from fluids and gases.
Air Particle Filter (Filter type). A filter used to remove particulates from air.
Compressed Air Filter (Filter type). A filter used to remove particulates from compressed air.
Odor Filter (Filter type). A filter used to remove odors from air.
Oil Filter (Filter type). A filter used to remove particulates from oil.
Strainer (Filter type). A filter used to remove particulates from a fluid.
Water Filter (Filter type). A filter used to remove particulates from water.
Fire Suppression Terminal. A fire suppression terminal has the purpose of delivering a fluid (gas or liquid) that will suppress a fire.

Breeching Inlet (Fire Suppression Terminal type). Symmetrical pipe fitting that unites two or more inlets into a single pipe. A breeching inlet may be used on either a wet or dry riser. Used by fire services personnel for fast connection of fire appliance hose reels. May also be used for foam.
Fire Hydrant (Fire Suppression Terminal type). Device, fitted to a pipe, through which a temporary supply of water may be provided.  May also be termed a stand pipe.
Fire Monitor (Fire Suppression Terminal type). Fire monitor.
Hose Reel (Fire Suppression Terminal type). A supporting framework on which a hose may be wound.
Sprinkler (Fire Suppression Terminal type). Device for sprinkling water from a pipe under pressure over an area.
Sprinkler Deflector (Fire Suppression Terminal type). Device attached to a sprinkler to deflect the water flow into a spread pattern to cover the required area.

Flow Controller. The distribution flow element IfcFlowController defines the occurrence of elements of a distribution system that are used to regulate flow through a distribution system. Examples include dampers, valves, switches, and relays. Its type is defined by IfcFlowControllerType or subtypes.

Flow Fitting. The distribution flow element IfcFlowFitting defines the occurrence of a junction or transition in a flow distribution system, such as an elbow or tee. Its type is defined by IfcFlowFittingType or its subtypes.
Flow Instrument. A flow instrument reads and displays the value of a particular property of a system at a point, or displays the difference in the value of a property between two points.
Ammeter (Flow Instrument type). A device that reads and displays the current flow in a circuit.
Combined (Flow instrument type). A device that reads and displays the value of multiple properties of a system at a point, or displays the difference in the value of a property between two points.
Frequency Meter (Flow Instrument type). A device that reads and displays the electrical frequency of an alternating current circuit.
Phase Angle Meter (Flow Instrument type). A device that reads and displays the phase angle of a phase in a polyphase electrical circuit.
Power Factor Meter (Flow Instrument type). A device that reads and displays the power factor of an electrical circuit.
Pressure Gauge (Flow Instrument type). A device that reads and displays a pressure value at a point or the pressure difference between two points.
Thermometer (Flow instrument type). A device that reads and displays a temperature value at a point.
Voltmeter (Flow Instrument type). A device that measures and displays the voltage in a circuit.
Voltmeter Peak (Flow Instrument type). A device that reads and displays the peak voltage in an electrical circuit.
Voltmeter RMS (Flow instrument type). A device that reads and displays the RMS (mean) voltage in an electrical circuit.
Flow Meter. A flow meter is a device that is used to measure the flow rate in a system.
Energy Meter (Flow Meter type). An electric meter or energy meter is a device that measures the amount of electrical energy supplied to or produced by a residence, business or machine.
Gas Meter (Flow meter type). A device that measures the quantity of a gas or fuel.
Oil Meter (Flow Meter type). A device that measures the quantity of oil.
Water Meter (Flow Meter type). A device that measures the quantity of water.

Flow Moving Device. The distribution flow element IfcFlowMovingDevice defines the occurrence of an apparatus used to distribute, circulate or perform conveyance of fluids, including liquids and gases (such as a pump or fan), and typically participates in a flow distribution system. Its type is defined by IfcFlowMovingDeviceType or its subtypes.
Flow Segment. The distribution flow element IfcFlowSegment defines the occurrence of a segment of a flow distribution system.

Flow Storage Device. The distribution flow element IfcFlowStorageDevice defines the occurrence of a device that participates in a distribution system and is used for temporary storage (such as a tank). Its type is defined by IfcFlowStorageDeviceType or its subtypes.

Flow Terminal. The distribution flow element IfcFlowTerminal defines the occurrence of a permanently attached element that acts as a terminus or beginning of a distribution system (such as an air outlet, drain, water closet, or sink). A terminal is typically a point at which a system interfaces with an external environment. Its type is defined by IfcFlowTerminalType or its subtypes.

Flow Treatment Device. The distribution flow element IfcFlowTreatmentDevice defines the occurrence of a device typically used to remove unwanted matter from a fluid, either liquid or gas, and typically participates in a flow distribution system. Its type is defined by IfcFlowTreatmentDeviceType or its subtypes.

Footing. A footing is a part of the foundation of a structure that spreads and transmits the load to the soil. A footing is also characterized as shallow foundation, where the loads are transferred to the ground near the surface.
Caisson Foundation (Footing type). A foundation construction type used in underwater construction.

Footing Beam (Footing type). Footing elements that are in bending and are supported clear of the ground. They will normally span between piers, piles or pile caps. They are distinguished from beams in the building superstructure since they will normally require a lower grade of finish. They are distinguished from STRIP_FOOTING since they are clear of the ground surface and hence require support to the lower face while the concrete is curing.
Pad Footing (Footing type). An element that transfers the load of a single column (possibly two) to the ground.
Pile Cap (Footing type). An element that transfers the load from a column or group of columns to a pier or pile or group of piers or piles.
Strip Footing (Footing type). A linear element that transfers loads into the ground from either a continuous element, such as a wall, or from a series of elements, such as columns.
Furniture. Furniture defines complete furnishings such as a table, desk, chair, or cabinet, which may or may not be permanently attached to a building structure.
Bed (Furniture type). Furniture for sleeping.
Chair (Furniture type). Furniture for seating a single person.
Desk (Furniture type). Furniture with a countertop and optional drawers for a single person.
